-- Canada Suspends License of XL Foods Alberta Meat Plant
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2012-09-28T15:23:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-28/canada-suspends-license-of-xl-foods-alberta-meat-plant.html
Canada’s Food Inspection Agency has
suspended the license of an XL Foods meat plant in  Alberta  until
it takes actions to deal with contamination.  The decision against the plant in Brooks, Alberta, was
announced at a press conference by Brian Evans, the country’s
chief veterinary officer. He said ongoing testing showed
bacteria in the facility.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Quinn in Ottawa at 
